          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":40,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"sunday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Easy long run at 5:52–6:43/km. Keep effort conversational — this is your aerobic foundation. Target 14 km, same as your current long run, so we're starting where you are and building confidence.\"},\"monday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest day. After Sunday's long run, your body needs time to begin the adaptation process. Rest is part of the training, not a break from it.\"},\"tuesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 5:52–6:43/km, ~8 km. Focus on relaxed breathing and smooth turnover. No watch-chasing — effort should feel genuinely comfortable.\"},\"wednesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"Tempo run at 4:53/km threshold pace. Warm up 10 min easy, then 20 min at threshold, cool down 10 min easy (~8 km total). This builds your lactate threshold — the key physiological driver for half marathon performance.\"},\"thursday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest or very light movement. Let Wednesday's quality work absorb. If you feel restless, a short walk is fine — keep it easy.\"},\"friday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 5:52–6:43/km, ~7 km. This is a recovery-oriented aerobic run — keep the effort low so you arrive at Saturday feeling fresh.\"},\"saturday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 5:52–6:43/km, ~3 km. Short, relaxed shakeout to round out the week. Legs should feel light — if not, shorten it without hesitation.\"},\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Lee. This opening week mirrors your recent training load — 40 km, 5 days — so there's no shock to your system, just structure and intention. The big idea this week is establishing your aerobic base and introducing a single quality session (Thursday tempo) to begin lifting your lactate threshold. Your 10K time of 48:00 tells us your current fitness is solid for an intermediate runner, and your 1:45 half marathon goal is genuinely achievable with smart, consistent progression over the next 16 weeks. Roughly 80% of your running this week is easy, which is right where it should be at this stage. The tempo on Wednesday is the one session to take seriously — everything else supports it.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
